%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20Iconic%20Singer%20Talat%20Mahmood%20Mesmerised%20Telugu%20Audience%2C%20Crowds%20at%20Royal%20Albert%20Hall%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17184624%2FFotoJet-5.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20are%20excerpts%20from%20the%20recently%20released%20book%3C%2Fem%3E%20Talat%20Mahmood%3A%20The%20Definitive%20Biography%20%3Cem%3Eby%20Sahar%20Zaman.%20February%202024%20marks%20the%20centenary%20birth%20anniversary%20of%20the%20yesteryear%20singer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPerfection%20in%20Telugu%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20wrapped%20up%20the%20final%20year%20of%20this%20golden%20decade%20with%20another%20feather%20in%20his%20cap.%20He%20sang%20for%20another%20regional%20film%2C%20this%20time%20in%20Telugu.%20The%20film%E2%80%99s%20name%20was%20%3Cem%3EManorama%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1959).%20He%20sang%20three%20songs%20with%20music%20composed%20by%20Ramesh%20Naidu.%20This%20is%20Talat%E2%80%99s%20solo%20song%20in%20the%20film%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Andala%20seema%20sudha%20nilayam%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EEe%20lokame%20Divya%20Prema%20mayam%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(This%20beautiful%20sweet%20abode%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20world%20is%20filled%20with%20divine%20love)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20music%20composer%20Ramesh%20Naidu%20knew%20Talat%20from%20his%20Calcutta%20days%20and%20he%20wanted%20all%20songs%20of%20the%20main%20lead%20sung%20by%20Talat.%20He%20was%20called%20to%20Chennai%20and%20rehearsals%20of%20all%20the%20songs%20would%20happen%20at%20the%20Taj%20Connemara%20Hotel%20where%20Talat%20was%20staying.%20It%20is%20often%20said%20that%20out%20of%20all%20the%20languages%20of%20South%20India%2C%20Telugu%20is%20the%20hardest.%20Despite%20Talat%20not%20knowing%20the%20language%20at%20all%2C%20Naidu%20was%20confident%20of%20his%20ability%20to%20sing%20comfortably%20in%20it.%20After%20all%2C%20he%20had%20witnessed%20how%20Talat%20had%20completely%20blended%20as%20a%20native%20speaker%20while%20singing%20in%20Bengali.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHis%20pronunciation%20was%20perfect.%20There%20was%20no%20hint%20of%20any%20non-native%20accent.%20It%20is%20especially%20difficult%20to%20do%20a%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Emurki%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(inverted%20mordent%20in%20music)%20on%20the%20right%20word%20to%20evoke%20the%20right%20feeling%2C%20when%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20the%20language.%20But%20he%20sang%20his%20%E2%80%98murki%E2%80%99%20just%20at%20the%20apt%20moment%E2%80%9D%2C%20adds%20his%20co-singer%2C%20P.%20Susheela.%20She%20is%20known%20as%20one%20of%20the%20tallest%20singing%20legends%20in%20the%20country%2C%20with%20a%20career%20spanning%20six%20decades%20across%20South%20Indian%20cinema.%20She%20has%20sung%20one%20duet%20with%20Talat%20in%20this%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20fortunately%20had%20the%20chance%20to%20speak%20with%20her%2C%20despite%20her%20frail%20condition%20but%20the%20mention%20of%20Talat%20brought%20in%20a%20rush%20of%20fond%20memories%20about%20him.%20%E2%80%9CHis%20ability%20to%20sing%20on%20the%20key%20was%20amazing.%20His%20voice%20never%20wavered%20in%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Eshruti%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20(musical%20pitches).%20When%20he%20hit%20the%20note%20on%20his%20harmonium%2C%20it%20was%20difficult%20to%20differentiate%20his%20voice%20from%20the%20harmonium%20key%20because%20his%20voice%20was%20in%20perfect%20alignment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalat%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EMarachi%20poyevemo%20mayani%20bhasalu%2C%20mankideyo%20sakhi%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(Did%20you%20forget%20our%20promises%2C%20hard%20to%20get%20over%20o%E2%80%99%20dear)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESusheela%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EMarachi%20poradoyi%20cheysina%20vhaasalu%2C%20aashalu%20masina%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(Should%20not%20forget%20the%20promises%20made%2C%20even%20if%20hopes%20dwindle)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20further%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CHis%20control%20over%20emotions%20was%20remarkable.%20It%20would%20never%20overflow.%20You%20never%20felt%20he%20was%20overtly%20weeping%20or%20wailing%20because%20if%20emotions%20overflow%2C%20the%20listeners%20lose%20touch%20with%20song.%20My%20favourite%20song%20of%20his%20has%20been%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EJaayen%20to%20jaayen%20kahaan%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20which%20he%20sang%20in%20absolute%20perfection.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalat%E2%80%99s%20personality%20had%20the%20gift%20of%20making%20personal%20connections%20and%20fond%20friendships%20with%20colleagues%20very%20soon.%20People%20would%20feel%20the%20warmth%20of%20his%20affection%20and%20genuine%20care.%20Another%20great%20singer%20of%20that%20time%20from%20the%20South%20Indian%20music%20industry%20was%20P.%20B.%20Sreenivas%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20PBS.%20He%20had%20once%20gone%20to%20visit%20Talat%20at%20his%20home%20in%20Bandra.%20Susheela%20recalls%20how%20PBS%20would%20often%20talk%20about%20that%20evening%20spent%20with%20Talat%20who%20sat%20with%20his%20harmonium%20and%20sang%20Ghazals%20for%20at%20least%20half%20an%20hour%20in%20honour%20of%20his%20visiting%20guest.%20PBS%20was%20mesmerised%20by%20his%20voice%20and%20touched%20by%20the%20gesture.%20He%20believed%20that%20there%20was%20no%20greater%20crooner%20than%20Talat%2C%20he%20was%20a%20natural%20in%20this%20genre%20and%20never%20required%20to%20scream%20out%20any%20emotions.%20Subtlety%20was%20his%20forte.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2050s%20was%20the%20most%20successful%20and%20significant%20decade%20in%20Talat%E2%80%99s%20career.%20The%2050s%20made%20him%20a%20superstar%20singer%20and%20a%20filmstar%20to%20the%20outside%20world%20and%20a%20complete%20family%20man%20at%20home.%20But%20there%20was%20never%20any%20time%20to%20take%20a%20breath%20and%20rest%20on%20some%20laurels.%20Talat%20didn%E2%80%99t%20believe%20in%20that.%20He%20was%20looking%20forward%20to%20the%201960s%20with%20more%20gusto%20and%20fervour.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Frank%20Sinatra%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%201968%2C%20Talat%20received%20an%20invitation%20for%20a%20recording%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20Times%20Square%20at%201481%20Broadway%20Studio.%20But%20this%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20for%20recording%20a%20song.%20He%20had%20been%20invited%20as%20a%20guest%20on%20the%20popular%20talk%20show%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98Joe%20Franklin%20Show%E2%80%99.%20The%20channel%20where%20this%20show%20was%20aired%20for%20decades%20was%20called%20WOR-TV%20with%20its%20recording%20studio%20called%20STUDIO-4%2C%20on%20the%20upper%20floor%20of%20the%20art%20deco%20Rialto%20Theatre.%20Nothing%20can%20beat%20the%20historic%20importance%20of%20this%20place%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20charming%20past%20of%20old%20Times%20Square.%20The%20show%20host%20Joe%20Franklin%20is%20credited%20for%20having%20the%20first%20ever%20talk%20show%20and%20was%20a%20pioneer%20in%20inventing%20the%20format%20of%20these%20one-on-one%20chats%20on%20television.%20The%20formula%20he%20created%20was%20about%20a%20curious%20show%20host%20sitting%20behind%20the%20desk%2C%20quizzing%20a%20range%20of%20personalities%20from%20varied%20professional%20fields.%20His%20show%20had%20an%20uninterrupted%20run%20from%201951%20to%201993%2C%20with%20stars%20ranging%20from%20Bing%20Crosby%2C%20Paul%20Newman%2C%20Al%20Pacino%2C%20Barbra%20Streisand%2C%20Michael%20Jackson%20and%20Woody%20Allen%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few.%20His%20envious%20list%20of%20guests%20also%20included%20Andy%20Warhol%2C%20Muhammad%20Ali%20and%20US%20Presidents%20like%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20and%20Richard%20Nixon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20picture%20of%20Talat%20standing%20with%20Franklin%20in%20his%20studio%20set%20with%20a%20background%20of%20abstract%20white%20and%20purple%20Mondrianesque%20triangles%20outlined%20in%20strong%2C%20black%20strokes.%20The%20audience%20immediately%20took%20note%20of%20this%20gentle%20legend%20from%20India%20when%20Franklin%20introduced%20him%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Frank%20Sinatra%20of%20India%E2%80%99.%20This%20was%20a%20comparison%20which%20stuck%20on%20for%20long%2C%20especially%20when%20both%20crooning%20legends%20passed%20away%20barely%20five%20days%20apart%20in%20the%20same%20year%20in%201998.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recording%20time%20of%20this%20episode%20with%20Franklin%20was%20about%20one%20hour%20long.%20His%20studio%20team%20had%20purchased%20a%20record%20of%20Talat%E2%80%99s%20songs%20to%20play%20out%20for%20the%20audience%20in%20between%20the%20interview.%20It%20was%20an%20amazing%20moment%20when%20an%20all%20American%20audience%20watched%20their%20favourite%20talk%20show%20host%20speak%20to%20a%20suave%20singer%20from%20India%2C%20while%20his%20songs%20in%20Urdu%20played%20out%20in%20between%20their%20conversation.%20Talat%20spoke%20about%20his%20music%20journey%20that%20had%20taken%20the%20Asian%20Diaspora%20by%20storm!%20The%20show%20was%20aired%20on%20August%2029%2C%201968.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20America%2C%20Talat%20heard%20about%20a%20new%20concept%20of%20film%20tourism%20that%20had%20gained%20popularity%20in%20the%20U.S.%20This%20was%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98Universal%20City%20Studio%20Tours%E2%80%99%20which%20was%20a%20ticketed%20trip%20inside%20the%20Universal%20Studios%20in%20California.%20This%20is%20that%20part%20of%20history%20in%20which%20tourism%20and%20cinema%20were%20linked%20together%20with%20ticket%20sales.%20Universal%20showed%20how%20a%20film%20tourist%20gaze%20can%20bring%20immediate%20commercial%20benefit.%20Actor%2C%20singer%20and%20radio%20artist%20Bob%20Hastings%20used%20to%20be%20a%20regular%20at%20the%20Universal%20Studios.%20It%20was%20one%20such%20day%20that%20Hastings%20found%20out%20about%20a%20big%20star%20visiting%20from%20India.%20He%20was%20eager%20to%20talk%20to%20him%20about%20the%20workings%20of%20showbiz%20in%20India.%20He%20was%20delighted%20to%20know%20that%20Talat%20was%20a%20singer%20too%20and%20shared%20his%20newly%20released%20music%20album%20called%20%E2%80%98Bob%20Hastings%20Sings%20for%20the%20Family%E2%80%99.%20Hastings%20recorded%20an%20impromptu%20chat%20with%20Talat%20about%20his%20career%20and%20some%20pictures%20of%20them%20were%20clicked%20together%20for%20the%20local%20press.%20This%20trip%20to%20the%20U.S.%20worked%20as%20a%20great%20teaser.%20There%20were%20bigger%20concerts%20by%20Talat%20coming%20up%20in%20the%20USA%20and%20UK%20for%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERoyal%20Albert%20Hall%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20unstinting%20love%20and%20accolades%20that%20kept%20Talat%20going.%20Refusing%20to%20rest%20on%20his%20laurels%2C%20he%20was%20still%20on%20the%20move.%20He%20was%20touring%20and%20performing%20and%20winning%20hearts%2C%20gaining%20new%20fans%20across%20the%20globe.%20His%20tour%20to%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20was%20landmark%2C%20just%20like%20the%20United%20States.%20The%20highlight%20of%20this%20tour%20was%20performing%20at%20the%20esteemed%20Royal%20Albert%20Hall%20(RAH)%20in%20London%20in%201979.%20Ever%20since%20its%20launch%20by%20Queen%20Victoria%20in%201871%2C%20it%20has%20remained%20a%20coveted%20venue%20with%20a%20seating%20of%20more%20than%206%2C000.%20Leading%20artists%20of%20different%20genres%20from%20across%20the%20world%20wait%20for%20a%20chance%20to%20be%20approved%20for%20the%20venue%2C%20the%20calendar%20of%20which%20remains%20packed%20every%20year.%20281%20Speeches%20have%20been%20given%20by%20Albert%20Einstein%2C%20events%20by%20boxer%20Muhammad%20Ali%2C%20performances%20by%20Eric%20Clapton%2C%20Pink%20Floyd%2C%20Andrew%20Lloyd%20Webber%E2%80%99s%20Phantom%20of%20the%20Opera%2C%20Beth%20Hart%2C%20Adele%2C%20PlayStation%20music%20concert%2C%2060%20years%20of%20James%20Bond%2C%20Hollywood%20film%20premiers%2C%20awards%20nights%2C%20just%20to%20name%20a%20few%20from%20a%20very%20long%20list%20of%20prestigious%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2027%2C%201979%2C%20as%20Talat%20walked%20down%20the%20maroon-coloured%20carpeted%20and%20circular%20corridor%20backstage%2C%20looking%20at%20all%20the%20framed%20images%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20previous%20performers%2C%20he%20was%20aware%20of%20the%20historicity%20of%20this%20moment.%20It%20is%20a%20dream%20come%20true%20for%20any%20performing%20artist%20worth%20his%2Fher%20salt.%20The%20majestic%20interiors%20of%20the%20amphitheatre%20under%20the%20glass%20dome%20designed%20in%20the%20Italian%20Renaissance%20style%20have%20been%20witness%20to%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20significant%20cultural%20events.%20To%20date%2C%20there%20are%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20Indian%20musicians%20and%20singers%20who%20have%20performed%20at%20the%20RAH.%20Talat%20stepped%20on%20stage%20to%20thunderous%20applause%2C%20waving%20to%20the%20crowd%20which%20was%20occupying%20the%20maroon%20swivel%20seats%20and%20balconies%20with%20little%20arches%20clad%20in%20maroon%20velvet%20curtains.%20All%20of%20this%20grandeur%20was%20placed%20180%20degrees%20around%20the%20singer%20while%20his%20back%20faced%20the%20grand%20pipe%20organ%20in%20the%20hall.%20Talat%20was%20always%20there%20to%20help%20his%20friends%20however%20possible.%20Work%20had%20entirely%20dried%20up%20for%20popular%20comedian%20actor%20Agha.%20Many%20would%20recall%20his%20roles%20in%20old%20films%20like%20Patita%2C%20Jugnu%2C%20etc.%20He%20decided%20to%20take%20Agha%20along%20as%20part%20of%20his%20troupe%20who%20became%20a%20popular%20presenter%20with%20the%20crowd%20for%20all%20his%20shows%20in%20the%20UK.%20After%20being%20introduced%20on%20stage%20by%20actor%20Agha%20as%20the%20King%20of%20Hearts%2C%20Talat%20stepped%20in%20and%20addressed%20the%20audience%20with%20a%20warm%20note%2C%20%E2%80%9CAapse%20mera%20purana%20rishta%20hai.%20Aapke%20saamne%20main%20ghair%20to%20nahin%20hoon.%3Cem%3E%20Aap%20ka%20purana%20gaane%20wala%20hoon%20jisko%20aap%20ne%20hamesha%20pasand%20kiya%20hai%2C%20shukriya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(I%20have%20an%20old%20connection%20with%20you.%20I%20am%20no%20stranger%20to%20you.%20I%E2%80%99m%20a%20singer%20familiar%20to%20you%2C%20whom%20you%20have%20always%20liked%2C%20thank%20you).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalat%20gave%20an%20interesting%20insight%20on%20how%20he%20connected%20with%20different%20generations%20through%20his%20stage%20concerts.%20He%20reminisced%20about%20the%20audience%20that%20he%20had%20met%20during%20his%20East%20Africa%20tour%20in%201956.%20After%20their%20forced%20exodus%20from%20Uganda%20and%20Kenya%20under%20the%20Idi%20Amin%20dictatorship%2C%20many%20of%20them%20settled%20in%20the%20UK.%20Many%20children%20who%20were%20part%20of%20his%20audience%20in%20East%20Africa%20were%20today%20attending%20Talat%E2%80%99s%20concert%20at%20the%20RAH%20as%20adults.%20One%20wonders%2C%20could%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20youngest%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Saunak%E2%80%99s%20parents%20have%20been%20in%20this%20audience%3F%20Quite%20possibly%2C%20yes!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20started%20the%20show%20with%20one%20of%20his%20favourite%20songs%20to%20set%20the%20mood%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EHain%20sabse%20madhur%20woh%20geet%20jinhe%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20film%20Patita%20(1953).%20Incredibly%2C%20despite%20all%20his%20film%20songs%20which%20were%20iconic%20hits%20and%20had%20become%20timeless%20classics%20by%20the%201970s%2C%20his%20foremost%20and%20first%20ever%20blockbuster%20of%20his%20career%20was%20a%20non-%20film%20ghazal%20which%20never%20failed%20to%20give%20Talat%20the%20loudest%20claps.%20Talat%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20Ghazal%20was%20released%20in%201944%20and%20it%20still%20sells%20like%20hot%20cakes%20to%20date%E2%80%9D.%20This%20ghazal%20was%20%E2%80%98Tasveer%20teri%20dil%20mera%20behla%20na%20sakegi%E2%80%99.%20The%20audience%20at%20the%20RAH%20wanted%20an%20encore%20after%20the%20ghazal%20but%20Talat%20apologised%20in%20order%20to%20move%20on%20to%20other%20songs.%20The%20restless%20audience%20always%20had%20to%20be%20pacified%20by%20Talat%20that%20their%20%E2%80%98farmaaish%E2%80%99%20(requested%20songs)%20would%20be%20sung%20by%20him%20as%20well%20but%20he%20would%20be%20unable%20to%20accommodate%20an%20encore%20for%20any%20song.%20But%20then%20guess%20what%3F%20The%20persuasive%20audience%20eventually%20got%20their%20way!%20Amidst%20the%20whistles%20and%20claps%2C%20Talat%20repeated%20the%20stanza%20of%20this%20song%20from%20the%20film%20Dil-e-Nadan%20(1953)%2C%20which%20was%20also%20his%20film%20as%20an%20actor%20in%20the%20main%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Bekhata%20tune%20mujh%20se%20khushi%20chheen%20li%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EZinda%20rakha%20magar%20zindagi%20chheen%20li%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EKar%20diya%20dil%20ka%20khun%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EChup%20kahaan%20tak%20rahun%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3ESaaf%20kyu%20na%20kahun%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3ETu%20khushi%20se%20meri%20dar%20gaya%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EZindagi%20dene%20wale%20sun%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(%3Cem%3EWhy%20have%20you%20snatched%20away%20my%20happiness%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EI%E2%80%99m%20alive%20but%20breathing%20without%20a%20soul%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EMy%20heart%20swims%20in%20blood%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3ETo%20what%20avail%20is%20my%20silence%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EIsn%E2%80%99t%20it%20crystal%20clear%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EYou%20are%20envious%20of%20my%20happiness%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EO%2C%20Giver%20of%20Life%2C%20hear%20me%20out%3C%2Fem%3E)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20ovation%20for%20him%20thundered%20down%2C%20he%20had%20just%20launched%20the%20musical%20equivalent%20of%20a%20grand%20slam.%20The%20audience%20joined%20in%20with%20a%20fresh%20jolt%20of%20delighted%20cheers.%20In%20the%20alchemy%20that%20a%20great%20performance%20can%20produce%2C%20Talat%20had%20united%20a%20houseful%20of%20strangers%20into%20celebrants%20in%20the%20borderless%20nation%20of%20music.%20His%20final%20song%20for%20the%20evening%20was%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EJhoome%20re%2C%20neela%20ambar%20jhoome%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20from%20the%20film%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EEk%20Gaon%20Ki%20Kahani%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99(1957).%20As%20Talat%20hummed%20away%20the%20last%20line%20of%20this%20peppy%20song%2C%20the%20applause%20didn%E2%80%99t%20stop.%20The%20crowd%20cheered%20louder%20for%20an%20encore.%20The%20British%20official%20from%20the%20RAH%20took%20over%20the%20mike%2C%20profusely%20apologising%20to%20the%20audience%20that%20the%20time%20is%20up%2C%20thanking%20Talat%20for%20the%20brilliant%20success%20of%20his%20show.%20It%20is%20believed%20that%20tickets%20to%20this%20concert%20were%20entirely%20sold%20out%20two%20weeks%20in%20advance.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708176256000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fwhen-iconic-singer-talat-mahmood-mesmerised-telugu-audience-crowds-at-royal-albert-hall%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sahar%20Zaman's%20latest%20book%20--%20Talat%20Mahmood%3A%20The%20Definitive%20Biography%20--%20explores%20the%20unknown%20facets%20of%20yesteryear%20singer's%20professional%20and%20personal%20life.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2218%20popular%20artists%20Noah%20Kahan%20has%20collaborated%20with%2C%20so%20far%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221685%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22noah%20kahan%20performing%20on%20stage%20with%20a%20spotify%20logo%20behind%20him%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ce6d36f533b039a8842beb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221264%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENoah%20Kahan%20released%20his%20%26quot%3BStick%20Season%26quot%3B%20album%20in%202022.%20%3Cp%3ECatherine%20Powell%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Spotify%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption