0on%20Foreign%20Relations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreedom%20Capital%20Markets%20chief%20global%20strategist%20Jay%20Woods%20took%20a%20similar%20stance%3A%20The%20economy%20is%20cooling%2C%20just%20not%20as%20quickly%20as%20many%20expected.%20He%20said%20a%20meaningful%20spike%20in%20CPI%20or%20PCE%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Fed's%20preferred%20inflation%20gauge%20%E2%80%94%20could%20cement%20the%20higher-for-longer%20argument%2C%20but%20so%20far%20that's%20not%20happened.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20still%20in%20the%20soft%20landing%20camp%2C%26quot%3B%20Woods%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThings%20may%20not%20be%20as%20smooth%20as%20people%20think%2C%20but%20even%20the%20thought%20of%20another%20rate%20hike%20would%20require%20an%20extreme%20shock%20to%20the%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EThe%20Fed's%20next%20move%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20for%20keeping%20rates%20unchanged%20has%20gained%20momentum%20over%20recent%20weeks%2C%20but%20both%20markets%20and%20the%20Fed%20ultimately%20expect%20easing%20interest%20rates%20in%202024.%20CME%20projections%20and%20policymakers'%20own%20dot%20plot%20projections%20say%20as%20much.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20has%20proved%20reliable%20and%20transparent%20in%20recent%20months%20about%20the%20central%20bank's%20outlook%2C%20and%20markets%20have%20responded%20with%20strong%20stock%20rallies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20blowout%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-labor-market-unemployment-rate-wage-growth-january-economy-2024-2%3Futm_source%3Dcopy-link%26utm_medium%3Dreferral%26utm_content%3Dtopbar%5C%22%3EJanuary%20jobs%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20hot%20CPI%20reading%20have%20fueled%20concerns%20of%20an%20overheating%20economy%2C%20but%20the%20retail%20sales%20data%20released%20Thursday%20pushed%20back%20on%20that%20thinking.%20January%20data%20came%20in%20softer%20than%20expected%2C%20dipping%200.8%25%20month-on-month%2C%20versus%20the%20expected%200.3%25%20decline.%3C%2F