A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170120%2FImage-7.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22849%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170120%2FImage-7.jpg%20849w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170120%2FImage-7-212x300.jpg%20212w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170120%2FImage-7-724x1024.jpg%20724w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697657%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EImage%208%3A%20Extract%20from%20BEL%E2%80%99s%20Complete%20Specifications%20of%20VVPAT%20machine%20submitted%20to%20the%20Patents%20Office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhich%20is%20the%20vote%20that%20must%20be%20counted%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReaders%2C%20wearied%20by%20all%20these%20technical%20details%2C%20may%20ask-%20%E2%80%9Cwhat%20is%20the%20point%20of%20all%20this%20argumentation%20and%20evidence-splashing%3F%E2%80%9D%20Well%2C%20the%20point%20is%20very%20simple%20and%20goes%20to%20the%20very%20heart%20of%20the%20demand%20made%20by%20several%20opposition%20political%20parties%20and%20civil%20society%20groups%20like%20the%20Citizens%20Commission%20on%20Elections%20(CCE)-%20all%20VVPAT%20slips%20must%20be%20counted%20rather%20than%20a%20small%20sample%20of%20five%20randomly%20chosen%20VVPAT%20units%20which%20the%20ECI%20has%20defended%20to%20be%20scientifically%20of%20adequate%20size%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20in%20its%20reply%20to%20FAQ%20%2362.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20electronic%20voting%20which%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cvote%E2%80%9D%20that%20must%20be%20counted%20on%20counting%20day%20after%20polling%20is%20over-%20is%20it%20the%20candidates%E2%80%99%20tally%20of%20votes%20as%20calculated%20by%20the%20CU%20or%20the%20VVPAT%20slips%20which%20the%20voters%20see%20and%20verify%20to%20their%20satisfaction%3F%20This%20is%20the%20question%20that%20many%20opposition%20leaders%20and%20CCE%20have%20posed%20to%20the%20ECI.%20ECI%20deals%20with%20this%20issue%20at%20FAQ%20%2363%20in%20this%20manner%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CQ63.%20The%20ECI%20has%20to%20define%20which%20one%20is%20true%20representation%20of%20the%20will%20of%20the%20voter%3F%20Vote%20recorded%20on%20Control%20Unit%20or%20voter%20verified%20SLIP%20in%20VVPAT%3F%20If%20Counting%20is%20based%20on%20the%20Control%20Unit%20count%20what%20is%20the%20use%20of%20Verifiable%20paper%20SLIP%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EAns.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20system%20of%20VVPAT%20has%20been%20introduced%20only%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20greater%20transparency%20and%20enhancing%20the%20confidence%20of%20voters%20by%20way%20of%20immediate%20verification%20of%20the%20printed%20ballot%20slip%20having%20the%20chosen%20candidate%E2%80%99s%20Name%2C%20Serial%20Number%20and%20Symbol%20and%20recording%20of%20vote%20in%20the%20Control%20Unit.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20per%20existing%20legislation%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3ERule%2056C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eof%20the%20Conduct%20of%20Elections%20(Amendment)%20Rules%20clearly%20states%20that%20after%20the%20returning%20officer%20is%20satisfied%20that%20a%20voting%20machine%20has%20not%20been%20tampered%20with%2C%20he%20shall%20have%20the%20votes%20counted%20by%20pressing%20the%20appropriate%20button%20marked%20%E2%80%9CResult%E2%80%9D%20provided%20in%20the%20control%20unit%20whereby%20the%20total%20votes%20polled%20and%20votes%20polled%20by%20each%20candidate%20shall%20be%20displayed%20in%20respect%20of%20each%20candidate%20on%20the%20display%20panel%20provided%20for%20the%20purpose%20in%20the%20unit.%20The%20candidate%20wise%20result%20so%20obtained%20from%20all%20control%20units%20used%20in%20the%20election%20is%20to%20be%20tabulated%20in%20a%20result%20sheet%20in%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EForm%2020%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eand%20the%20particulars%20so%20entered%20in%20the%20result%20sheet%20announced.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EContesting%20candidates%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20request%20for%20the%20VVPAT%20slip%20count%20under%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3ERule%2056D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eof%20the%20Conduct%20of%20Elections%20Rules%2C%201961%20after%20completion%20of%20counting%20of%20votes%20from%20the%20EVMs.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3ERule%2056D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E(4)%20(b)%20clearly%20states%20that%20in%20case%20of%20a%20discrepancy%20between%20the%20Electronic%20Count%20in%20the%20Control%20Unit%20and%20the%20ballot%20slip%20count%20of%20the%20VVPAT%2C%20the%20VVPAT%20slip%20count%20shall%20prevail.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20at%20paragraph%20%3Cstrong%3Eno.%2000116%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20of%20the%20Complete%20Specifications%20submitted%20to%20the%20Patents%20Office%20BEL%20makes%20the%20following%20assertion%20about%20what%20is%20the%20vote%20(see%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EImage%209%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebelow)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%5B00116%5D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20this%20manner%2C%20proposed%20system%20can%20faithfully%20record%20the%20%3Cu%3Edigital%20choice%20(vote%20being%20cast)%20of%20the%20voter%20(using%20the%20BU%20of%20the%20associated%20EVM)%3C%2Fu%3E%20%3Cu%3Ein%20form%20of%20a%20printed%20ballot%20slip%20that%20is%20directly%20and%20easily%20understood%20by%20the%20voter%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20voter%20has%20exercised%20his%2Fher%20digital%20choice%3C%2Fu%3E%3B%20and%20thereafter%20store%20the%20printed%20ballot%20slip%20at%20a%20secure%20location%20for%20further%20audit%20if%20required.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E(emphasis%20supplied)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20it%20not%20the%20digital%20choice%20of%20the%20voter%20as%20recorded%20by%20the%20VVPAT%20on%20paper%20which%20must%20be%20counted%2C%20and%20not%20merely%20the%20electronic%20data%20recorded%20in%20the%20CU%20which%20the%20voter%20will%20never%20get%20to%20see%20at%20the%20polling%20booth%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170454%2FImage-9.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22849%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170454%2FImage-9.jpg%20849w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170454%2FImage-9-212x300.jpg%20212w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170454%2FImage-9-724x1024.jpg%20724w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697660%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3A%20Extract%20from%20BEL%E2%80%99s%20Complete%20Specifications%20of%20the%20VVPAT%20machine%20submitted%20to%20the%20Patents%20Office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20beginning%20of%20this%20piece%2C%20I%20raised%20these%20questions-%20%E2%80%9Ccan%20it%20then%20be%20said%20that%20the%20voter%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20know%20is%20limited%20to%20accessing%20details%20about%20the%20public%20character%20of%20electoral%20candidates%20and%20nothing%20more%20relating%20to%20the%20electoral%20process%3F%20Does%20it%20not%20extend%20to%20seeking%20adequate%20knowledge%20about%20the%20current%20voting%20system%20which%20is%20facilitated%20through%20machines%20unlike%20the%20paper-based%20system%20that%20was%20the%20primary%20balloting%20method%20until%20a%20decade%20ago%3F%20When%20I%20began%20writing%20this%20piece%2C%20these%20questions%20were%20open-ended.%20However%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Constitution%20Bench%20which%20struck%20down%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20route%20of%20funding%20political%20parties%20has%20answered%20them%20conclusively.%20While%20concurring%20with%20the%20judgement%20(%3Cem%3EAssociation%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20%26amp%3B%20Ar.%2C%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E)%20authored%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D%20Y%20Chandrachud%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20Bench%2C%20Justice%20Khanna%20in%20his%20separate%20opinion%20says-%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C19.%20%3Cu%3EThe%20right%20to%20vote%20is%20a%20constitutional%20and%20statutory%20right%2C%E2%80%A6%20grounded%20in%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20as%20the%20casting%20of%20a%20vote%20amounts%20to%20expression%20of%20an%20opinion%20by%20the%20voter%E2%80%A6%20The%20citizens%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20know%20stems%20from%20this%20very%20right%2C%20as%20meaningfully%20exercising%20choice%20by%20voting%20requires%20information%3C%2Fu%3E.%20Representatives%20elected%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20votes%20cast%20in%20their%20favour%2C%20enact%20new%2C%20and%20amend%20existing%20laws%2C%20and%20when%20in%20power%2C%20take%20policy%20decisions.%20%3Cu%3EAccess%20to%20information%20which%20can%20materially%20shape%20the%20citizens%E2%80%99%20choice%20is%20necessary%20for%20them%20to%20have%20a%20say%20in%20how%20their%20lives%20are%20affected%3C%2Fu%3E.%20%3Cu%3EThus%2C%20the%20right%20to%20know%20is%20paramount%20for%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20and%20democracy%3C%2Fu%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20(emphasis%20supplied)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20records%20the%20views%20of%20the%20Constitution%20Bench%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20voters%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20know%20in%20the%20following%20words%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C77.%20The%20following%20principles%20can%20be%20deduced%20from%20the%20decisions%20of%20this%20Court%20in%20ADR%20(supra)%20and%20PUCL%20(supra)%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%20The%20right%20to%20information%20of%20voters%20which%20is%20traced%20to%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20is%20built%20upon%20the%20jurisprudence%20of%20both%20the%20first%20and%20the%20second%20phases%20in%20the%20evolution%20of%20the%20doctrine%2C%20identified%20above.%20%3Cu%3EThe%20common%20thread%20of%20reasoning%20which%20runs%20through%20both%20the%20first%20and%20the%20second%20phases%20is%20that%20information%20which%20furthers%20democratic%20participation%20must%20be%20provided%20to%20citizens.%20Voters%20have%20a%20right%20to%20information%20which%20would%20enable%20them%20to%20cast%20their%20votes%20rationally%20and%20intelligently%20because%20voting%20is%20one%20of%20the%20foremost%20forms%20of%20democratic%20participation%3C%2Fu%3E%3B%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20(emphasis%20supplied)%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20issues%20discussed%20above%20are%20just%20a%20sample%20of%20the%20multiple%20doubts%20that%20crop%20up%20when%20the%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20answers%20to%20FAQs%20are%20compared%20with%20the%20contents%20of%20other%20publicly%20available%20documents%20about%20the%20EVM-VVPAT%20combo.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20must%20be%20said%2C%20our%20doubts%20will%20not%20go%20away%20by%20simply%20admonishing%20or%20ignoring%20them.%20The%20levels%20of%20transparency%20that%20the%20ECI%20has%20adopted%20are%20hopelessly%20inadequate%20to%20meet%20the%20very%20high%20standards%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20has%20set%20for%20our%20right%20to%20know%2C%20as%20citizen-voters.%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVenkatesh%20Nayak%20is%20Director%2C%20Commonwealth%20Human%20Rights%20Initiative%2C%20New%20Delhi.%20All%20facts%20narrated%20above%20are%20in%20the%20public%20domain.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708172596000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10211621%2FEffect-2024-02-10T202212.238.png%2